title: Code.org
description:
Code.orgÂ® is a nonprofit dedicated to expanding access to computer science and AI in schools and increasing participation by young women and students from other underrepresented groups.  Our vision is that every student in every school should have the opportunity to learn computer programming. We believe computer science and AI should be part of the core curriculum in education, alongside other science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM) courses, such as biology, physics, chemistry and algebra.

Code.org is a 501c3 tax-exempt organization.
